&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I have changed the dictionary that converts the QS news. You will notice
&gt; &gt; that the combination that was formerly Ado Roar is now just plain Roar.
&gt; &gt; So the word &quot;utter&quot; should not appear as:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Ado Tut Roar
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I made this change to test out a new way of handling the ambiguous
&gt; &gt; combination of &quot;ar,&quot; when forming the sound in &quot;bird&quot; or &quot;nurse.&quot; We had
&gt; &gt; situation in which the word &quot;arrest&quot; and &quot;urban&quot; both started with Ado
&gt; &gt; Roar, but each had a very different sound. Anthony has made a suggestion
&gt; &gt; to simply get rid of the vowel before the &quot;r&quot; in words like &quot;urban,&quot; but
&gt; &gt; to keep it for words like &quot;arrest.&quot;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; This is just an experiment as we try to work out a solution, so let me
&gt; &gt; know any difficulties you have, and what you think.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Paul
